name: Aether The Void Between Worlds
description: With the theme "Fifth Element" I had to put away my multipass and do some research. Turns out medieval scientists believed in a fifth element they called "Aether" (pronounced Ee-ther). Their definition of it being an element that exists between voids and binds them together, which is shockingly similar to the concept of gravity (aside from Gravity, you know, not actually being a material thing). So I went with it!
